[[File:Hallowed mark detail.png|left|120px]]
'''Hallowed marks''' are the reward currency gained by looting [[Coffin (Hallowed Sepulchre)|coffins]] within the [[Hallowed Sepulchre]] in [[Darkmeyer]]. These can be used at the [[Mysterious Hallowed Goods]] shop.

Hallowed marks were the currency of [[Hallowvale]] during the [[Second Age]] and early [[Third Age]].{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ed|url=https://twitter.com/JagexEd/status/1269923632438009856|date=5 June 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/7D282|archivedate=8 June 2020|quote=It was the currency used there in the 2nd Age and early 3rd Age.}}

==Uses==
{| class="wikitable align-center-1 align-center-3"
! colspan="2" |Reward
! style="white-space:nowrap;" |Cost in {{plinkp|Hallowed mark}}
!Description
|-
|{{plinkt|Hallowed crystal shard|txt=Hallowed&nbsp;crystal&nbsp;shard}}
|{{Currency|Hallowed mark|1}}
|Used to teleport to the Hallowed Sepulchre lobby. They can be purchased from the [[Mysterious Hallowed Goods]] shop.
|-
|{{plinkt|Hallowed token}}
|{{Currency|Hallowed mark|10}}
|This token, when consumed within the Hallowed Sepulchre, will add an extra minute to the remaining time.
|-
|{{plinkt|Hallowed sack}}
|{{Currency|Hallowed mark|100}}
|When opened, hallowed sacks give loot found in coffins within the Hallowed Sepulchre.
|-
|{{plinkt|Hallowed grapple}}
|{{Currency|Hallowed mark|100}}
|This grapple, when equipped in the ammo slot, will always succeed grappling a [[Pillar (Hallowed Sepulchre)|Pillar]] in the Hallowed Sepulchre.<br/>This grapple cannot be used anywhere outside of the crypt.
|-
|{{plinkt|Hallowed focus}}
|{{Currency|Hallowed mark|100}}
|This focus, when equipped in the off-hand slot, will remove the chance of failure when conjuring [[Portal Frame]]s in the Hallowed Sepulchre.
|-
|{{plinkt|Hallowed symbol}}
|{{Currency|Hallowed mark|100}}
|This symbol, when equipped in the necklace slot, will halve the number of sacrifices required to a [[Saradomin Brazier]] in the Hallowed Sepulchre.
|-
|{{plinkt|Hallowed hammer}}
|{{Currency|Hallowed mark|100}}
|This hammer will never break nails when repairing [[Bridge (Hallowed Sepulchre)|Broken Bridge]]s in the Hallowed Sepulchre.
|-
|{{plinkt|Hallowed ring}}
|{{Currency|Hallowed mark|250}}
|This ring, when equipped in the ring slot, will prevent the user from losing time and taking damage when they fail an obstacle.<br/>It will "teleport them in the nick of time" and send them back to the start of the obstacle avoiding the time penalty, and eliminating the need to bring food.
|-
|{{plinkt|Dark dye}}
|{{Currency|Hallowed mark|300}}
|This dye can be used on any piece of graceful armour to recolour it into a dark graceful piece of armour.<br/>A total of 6 Dark dyes are needed to recolour the full graceful set, costing a total of {{Currency|Hallowed mark|1800}} hallowed marks.
|-
|{{plinkt|Dark acorn}}
|{{Currency|Hallowed mark|3000}}
|This acorn, when used on the [[Giant squirrel|Giant Squirrel]] pet, will turn it into a [[Giant squirrel#Dark|black and red version]] to match the dark graceful set.<br/>It is a permanent unlock and can be toggled back to its original colour at any time.
|}

==Item sources==
Hallowed marks can be obtained from both [[Coffin (Hallowed Sepulchre)|coffins]], as well as the [[Grand Hallowed Coffin]] at varying rates.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Husky|url=https://twitter.com/JagexHusky/status/1273653084334493696|date=18 June 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.vn/j7M8F|archivedate=18 June 2020|quote=Well, it's my birthday tomorrow and scuffed flames appear to be fixed so I'm in a good mood. As a result here's the ever so requested droprates from the sepulchre put together nicely on these images by @JagexRy}}
